<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="112" /> The <hi rend="italics">Constitutionalist</hi> devotes its <num value="1" type="ordinal">first</num> <num value="3">three</num> columns to a consideration of the actual state of affairs in <placeName reg="America, Pulaski, Illinois" key="tgn,2026331" authname="tgn,2026331">America</placeName> — The article, which is in very prominent type, is signed by <persName n="Mmayrac,,M.,Paulin,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00022" reg="default:Mmayrac,M.,Paulin,," authname="mmayrac,m.,paulin"><foreName full="yes">M.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">Paulin</foreName> <surname full="yes">Mmayrac</surname></persName>.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="113" />It does not deny that the capture of New Orleans is a great victory for the <rs>North</rs>, but adds: </p> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="114" /> What does this victory prove?

