<div3 type="orders" n="1" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><orgName><rs type="role" reg="Adjutant General">Adjutant General</rs>'s office</orgName>,<lb /><date value="1862-06-16" authname="1862-06-16">June 16, 1862.</date></head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="835" /> the several persons who have been authorized to recruit men for the <rs type="place">Line of State Troops</rs>, under the provisions of the <name>Act</name> of Assembly of <date value="1862-05-15" authname="1862-05-15">May 15, 1862.</date> are required to discontinue recruiting in the city of <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName> immediately.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="836" />Recruits not yet inspected are to be presented at this office for inspection by or before the <dateStruct value="--18" full="yes" authname="---18"><day reg="18" full="yes">18th inst.</day></dateStruct>, after which no subsistence or transportation will be allowed. </p> <closer> By order of the <rs>Governor</rs>. <lb /> <signed><persName n="Richardson,,William,H.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00321" reg="default:Richardson,William,H.,," authname="richardson,william,h."><foreName n="William" full="yes">Wm.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Richardson</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> je <num value="17">17</num>--3t <rs type="role" reg="Adjutant General">Adjutant General</rs>. </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="2" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><orgName><rs type="role" reg="Adjutant General">Adjutant General</rs>'s office</orgName>,<lb /><date value="1862-06-16" authname="1862-06-16">June 16, 1862.</date></head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="837" /> <persName n="Wilkins,Major,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00322" reg="mostcommon:Wilkins,nomatch:0" authname="wilkins"><roleName n="Major" full="yes">Major</roleName> <surname full="yes">Wilkins</surname></persName>, commanding the <num value="2" type="ordinal">second</num> class militia of the city of <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, will dotted an officer and guard from his command, with orders to visit all stores and other places of mercantile business, which have not been or are not closed according to order at <time value="2pm">2 o'clock P. M.</time>, and unless the proprietors shall conform promptly to that order, to place them under arrest and report. </p> <closer> By command. <lb /> je <num value="17">17</num>--3t <signed><persName n="Richardson,,William,H.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00323" reg="default:Richardson,William,H.,," authname="richardson,william,h."><foreName n="William" full="yes">Wm.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">H.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Richardson</surname></persName>, A. G.</signed> </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="3" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head rend="smallcaps">Headq'rs <orgName type="regiment" n="Reg. 3">3d Reg.</orgName> Va, infantry.<lb />Camp near <placeName reg="Richmond, Richmond, Virginia" key="tgn,7013964" authname="tgn,7013964">Richmond</placeName>, <date value="1862-06-16" authname="1862-06-16">16th June, 1862.</date></head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="838" />All officers who are absent from this command, for whatever cause, are hereby ordered to report at once to their companies for duty, or else send every week a certificate of unfitness from some Army <rs type="role" reg="Surgeon">Surgeon</rs> of <hi rend="italics">good standing;</hi> otherwise, they will be published as deserters, and their names stricken from the rolls. </p> <closer> <signed><persName n="Mayo,,Joseph,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00324" reg="default:Mayo,Joseph,,," authname="mayo,joseph"><foreName n="Joseph" full="yes">Jos.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Mayo</surname>, <genName n="junior" full="yes">Jr.</genName></persName>, <persName n="Com,Colonel,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00325" reg="mostcommon:Com,nomatch:0" authname="com"><roleName n="Colonel" full="yes">Col.</roleName> <surname full="yes">Com</surname></persName>'g.</signed> <lb /> <orgName n="Petersburg Express" type="newspaper">Petersburg Express</orgName> copy the above. <lb /> je <num value="17">17</num>--6t </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="4" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head type="nobreak">Attention, <orgName type="company" n="Company B">Company B</orgName>.</head> 
<p rend="nobreak">

<milestone unit="sentence" n="839" /> --Members of <orgName type="company" n="Company B">Company B</orgName>, will meet punctually at the <rs type="place">Confederate Prison</rs>, at <time value="11am">11 o'clock A. M.</time>, this morning, (<dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Tuesday</day></dateStruct>,) for the purpose of holding an election for officers.

<milestone unit="sentence" n="840" />A full attendance is requested.--The company will leave on <dateStruct full="yes"><day type="name" full="yes">Wednesday</day></dateStruct> <time>morning</time>, at <time value="7oclock">7 o'clock</time>, for the <orgName type="mil" key="MDRegiment">Maryland Regiment</orgName> in <orgName n="command"><persName n="Jackson,General,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00326" reg="nearbymention:Jackson,Stonewall,,," authname="jackson,stonewall"><roleName n="General" full="yes">Gen.</roleName> <surname full="yes">Jackson</surname></persName>'s command</orgName>. </p> <closer> je <num value="17">17</num>--1t </closer> </div3> 
<div3 type="orders" n="5" org="uniform" sample="complete"> 
<head><placeName reg="Royster Hospital">Royster Hospital</placeName>, <date value="1862-06-16" authname="1862-06-16">June 16, 1862.</date></head> 
<p>

<milestone unit="sentence" n="841" /> this is to certify that <persName n="Harris,,M.,W.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00327" reg="expanded:Harris,Marcellus,W.,," authname="harris,marcellus,w."><foreName full="yes">M.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">W.</foreName> <surname full="yes">Harris</surname></persName>, private in <orgName n="Artillery Company" type="company"><persName n="Thomas,,,,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00328" reg="nearbymention:Thomas,Edward,L.,," authname="thomas,edward,l."><surname full="yes">Thomas</surname></persName> Artillery company</orgName>, was a patient under my charge for several weeks, and owing to the fact that his health was rather precarious for camp service, he has been regularly detailed for service in this Hospital, </p> <closer> by order of <rs type="role" reg="Secretary of War">Secretary of War</rs>. <lb /> <signed><persName n="Harrison,,V.,W.,," id="n-0001.0000.00000.00329" reg="default:Harrison,V.,W.,," authname="harrison,v.,w."><foreName full="yes">V.</foreName> <foreName full="yes">W.</foreName>  <surname full="yes">Harrison</surname></persName>,</signed> <lb /> je <num value="17">17</num>--6t Ass't <rs type="role2">Surgeon</rs> in charge. </closer> </div3> </div2> 
